I should know the man's name.

284
00:15:43,845 --> 00:15:46,846
- Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
- He's stalking you?

285
00:15:46,915 --> 00:15:49,176
- Are you kidding me?
- You're dating the madman...

286
00:15:49,250 --> 00:15:52,251
who's trying to kill me?
- Why didn't you tell me his name?

287
00:15:52,320 --> 00:15:54,547
Last night he accused me
of seeing someone else.

288
00:15:54,622 --> 00:15:57,020
- He said, "Tell me his name!"
- He said that?

289
00:15:57,091 --> 00:15:59,250
If he sees us, can you imagine
what he'll do?

290
00:15:59,327 --> 00:16:01,861
If he thinks I ruined his NBC deal
and stole his girl!

291
00:16:01,930 --> 00:16:04,965
- That will be a kibosh for sure.
- What about me?

292
00:16:05,033 --> 00:16:06,725
Excuse me.

293
00:16:07,268 --> 00:16:09,802
Come on. This is Pavarotti.

294
00:16:10,071 --> 00:16:12,605
Three hundred dollars.
That's a lot of money.

295
00:16:12,674 --> 00:16:15,834
Steven Holtzman did a production
in Tunis last year.

296
00:16:15,910 --> 00:16:19,571
From what I understand,
the Muslims really took to it.

297
00:16:19,814 --> 00:16:23,816
I'll tell you what. You seem like a
nice guy. Let's stop jerking around.

298
00:16:24,152 --> 00:16:28,484
Give me $250. I got people waiting
for me. I gotta get the hell out of here.

299
00:16:28,656 --> 00:16:31,623
Scalping. I told them
to put on extra security.

300
00:16:31,693 --> 00:16:33,226
Excuse me.

301
00:16:33,461 --> 00:16:36,223
Pop, would you buzz off?
I got something cooking here.

302
00:16:36,297 --> 00:16:38,592
- Costanza?
- Mr. Reichman?

303
00:16:38,666 --> 00:16:40,825
Still a sewer-mouth.
Give me those tickets.

304
00:16:40,902 --> 00:16:46,565
Harold, don't. Harold, be careful
of your hair transplant!

305
00:16:46,641 --> 00:16:49,232
Anything is welcome.
I accept change.

306
00:16:49,310 --> 00:16:52,243
I don't have anything.
I gave it to that guy.

307
00:16:54,048 --> 00:16:56,514
You know, you could just say no.

308
00:16:56,584 --> 00:16:58,117
You don't have to humiliate me.

309
00:16:58,186 --> 00:17:01,653
I may be dressed as a clown,
but I am a person.

310
00:17:01,723 --> 00:17:04,348
- The guy took...
- I don't need people like you...

311
00:17:04,425 --> 00:17:06,083
looking down their noses at me.

312
00:17:06,160 --> 00:17:10,253
I am just a street performer
trying to make enough to get by.

313
00:17:10,331 --> 00:17:12,899
Doctor, is there a doctor anywhere?

314
00:17:12,967 --> 00:17:14,591
We need a doctor!

315
00:17:14,669 --> 00:17:18,136
What are you, showing off
for your girlfriend here, is that it?

316
00:17:18,206 --> 00:17:22,333
I'm not his girlfriend. We dated
for a while but things didn't work out.

317
00:17:22,610 --> 00:17:25,611
You people make me sick.

318
00:17:28,950 --> 00:17:32,019
That is one angry clown.

319
00:17:32,086 --> 00:17:34,051
The hardest part
about being a clown...

320
00:17:34,122 --> 00:17:37,953
it seems to me, would be that you're
constantly referred to as a clown.

321
00:17:38,026 --> 00:17:40,560
"Who is that clown?
I'm not working with that clown.

322
00:17:40,628 --> 00:17:42,161
Did you hire that clown?

323
00:17:42,230 --> 00:17:43,729
The guy's a clown."

324
00:17:43,831 --> 00:17:45,796
How do you even start into
being a clown?

325
00:17:45,867 --> 00:17:47,696
How do you know you
wanna be a clown?

326
00:17:47,769 --> 00:17:50,667
I guess you just get to a point
where your pants look so bad...

327
00:17:51,205 --> 00:17:53,273
it's actually easier
to become a clown...

328
00:17:53,341 --> 00:17:55,568
than having the proper alterations
done.

329
00:17:55,810 --> 00:17:59,744
If you think about it, a clown,
if there isn't a circus around them...

330
00:17:59,814 --> 00:18:02,348
is really just a very annoying person.

331
00:18:02,417 --> 00:18:05,884
I mean, you're in the back seat
of this guy's Volkswagen...

332
00:18:05,953 --> 00:18:09,352
"What, you're picking somebody
else up? Oh, man."

333
00:18:09,690 --> 00:18:12,816
I got one. Who needs one?
Pagliacci. Pagliacci.

334
00:18:13,127 --> 00:18:15,491
The tragic clown. Pagliacci...

335
00:18:19,934 --> 00:18:21,797
What did you say?

336
00:18:22,703 --> 00:18:24,464
What, are you a cop?

337
00:18:25,373 --> 00:18:27,202
No. I'm a clown.

338
00:18:28,776 --> 00:18:30,844
Man, you look familiar.

339
00:18:31,946 --> 00:18:33,513
You ever been to the circus?

340
00:18:34,082 --> 00:18:36,548
- Well, when I was a kid.
- Did you like it?

341
00:18:36,617 --> 00:18:39,185
Well, it was fun.

342
00:18:39,754 --> 00:18:42,414
Was kind of scared of the clowns.

343
00:18:43,758 --> 00:18:46,224
Are you still scared of clowns?

344
00:18:47,428 --> 00:18:49,086
Yeah.

345
00:18:51,632 --> 00:18:53,097
We're gonna miss the overture.

346
00:18:53,167 --> 00:18:59,638
Overture, curtains, lights
This is it, we'll hit the heights

347
00:18:59,707 --> 00:19:05,973
And, oh, what heights we'll hit
On with the show, this is it

348
00:19:09,717 --> 00:19:12,411
You know, it is so sad.

349
00:19:12,487 --> 00:19:15,613
All your knowledge of high culture
comes from Bugs Bunny cartoons.

350
00:19:17,692 --> 00:19:20,886
Oh, there's that clown again.
What does he want from me?

351
00:19:21,095 --> 00:19:23,390
Look, I'm serious.
I don't have the quarter.

352
00:19:23,464 --> 00:19:26,124
- That guy took it.
- I don't want any money.

353
00:19:27,869 --> 00:19:30,062
I smell cherry.

354
00:19:32,406 --> 00:19:34,940
- It's Binaca.
- Binaca?

355
00:19:39,914 --> 00:19:41,242
Go! Go!

356
00:19:41,415 --> 00:19:44,916
- All right, what did we say, 275?
- Two fifty.

357
00:19:45,453 --> 00:19:48,920
- Two fifty? Are you sure?
- Yeah, yeah, I'm sure.

358
00:19:49,290 --> 00:19:51,756
- All right. All right, 250.
- George!

359
00:19:52,293 --> 00:19:54,361
- Susan.
- I don't believe it.

360
00:19:54,428 --> 00:19:56,587
I'm so glad I caught you.

361
00:19:56,831 --> 00:19:59,491
What are you doing here?
You were going to the airport.

362
00:19:59,567 --> 00:20:01,862
